PaymentModel.s1Content:
All payments on FoxyPlay are made between users.

FoxyPlay:

is not the seller or buyer of digital assets;
is not a payment institution or bank;
does not provide financial or escrow services;
does not own or control users' digital assets.

The Platform only provides technical infrastructure for executing user-to-user transactions.

PaymentModel.s3Content:
User balances on FoxyPlay represent internal accounting records of amounts available for withdrawal based on completed P2P transactions.

Until withdrawal:

funds may be processed or held via the Operator's bank/payment accounts;
funds are not considered transferred to the user outside the Platform;
the user has a right to request payout subject to Platform rules and compliance checks.

FoxyPlay does not provide custodial wallet, deposit, or escrow services.

PaymentModel.s4Content:
Payouts to sellers are performed after:

transaction completion confirmation, or
expiration of the confirmation period.

Payout timing may depend on:

security checks;
fraud prevention;
compliance (AML/KYC);
payment provider requirements.

The Platform may delay or refuse payouts in accordance with its Terms and Compliance Policies.

PaymentModel.s5Content:
FoxyPlay may charge service fees for:

facilitating transactions;
payment processing;
payouts;
marketplace services.

Fees are displayed on the Platform.

PaymentModel.s6Content:
FoxyPlay acts exclusively as:

a technology marketplace operator;
a transaction recording system;
a risk and compliance controller.

FoxyPlay is not a financial intermediary and does not provide payment services to the public.

HowItWorks.s1Content:
Users may offer and purchase:

in-game items;
game currency;
gaming accounts;
boosting or gaming services;
other digital gaming assets permitted by Platform rules.

All listings are created by users.

HowItWorks.s2Content:
Transactions occur directly between users.

FoxyPlay:

does not sell digital assets;
does not purchase digital assets;
does not guarantee delivery;
is not a party to user agreements.

The Platform provides only technical marketplace functionality.

HowItWorks.s3Content:
To support safe trading, FoxyPlay provides:

transaction recording;
order tracking;
completion confirmation;
internal balance accounting;
dispute assistance tools;
fraud and risk monitoring.

These tools help facilitate user-to-user transactions but do not create financial custody.

HowItWorks.s4Content:
When a transaction is completed:

the buyer receives the digital asset/service;
the seller receives balance credit;
the seller may request payout;
the Platform records the transaction history.

HowItWorks.s5Content:
FoxyPlay does not control:

game publishers or developers;
game account ownership rights;
third-party platform rules;
external service availability.

Game publishers may restrict or prohibit asset transfers independently of FoxyPlay.

HowItWorks.s6Content:
To maintain marketplace safety, FoxyPlay may:

verify users (KYC);
monitor transactions;
block suspicious activity;
suspend accounts;
hold balances during review.

These measures are described in Terms and Compliance Policies.

OperatorLegal.s1Content:
The Operator acts as the provider of the FoxyPlay online marketplace infrastructure.

The Operator:

operates and maintains the Platform;
provides technical marketplace services;
maintains internal transaction accounting;
performs compliance and risk controls;
facilitates payouts from user balances.

The Operator does not act as a seller, buyer, broker, or financial institution.

OperatorLegal.s2Content:
FoxyPlay provides:

digital marketplace infrastructure;
listing and ordering systems;
transaction recording;
internal balance accounting;
payout processing;
compliance and safety controls.

Services are provided on a P2P marketplace basis.

Terms.s2Content:
The Platform is a technological online service that enables posting of information and interaction between users for the purpose of concluding agreements on digital assets.

The Operator:

is not a seller or buyer of assets;
is not a party to agreements between users;
is not a financial institution or payment organization;
does not provide banking or payment services;
does not professionally hold users' funds or crypto assets;
does not manage users' assets.

The Platform provides solely the technical infrastructure for the performance of agreements between users.

Terms.s3Content:
Transactions on the Platform may relate to:

digital in-game items;
game currency;
accounts;
game-related services;
other digital assets permitted by the Platform's rules.

The Operator does not guarantee the lawfulness of use of digital assets in video games or third-party services and is not liable for sanctions, blocking, or restrictions applied by rights holders.

Terms.s4Content:
The Platform may provide technical processing of payments related to the performance of agreements between users.

Crypto assets may be used by users as a means of settlement within such agreements.

The Platform:

does not open accounts or wallets for users;
does not provide crypto asset custody services;
does not manage crypto assets;
does not guarantee the stability of the value of crypto assets.

Crypto asset transactions may be irreversible and involve high risks.

Terms.s6Content:
In the course of performing agreements, the Platform may temporarily hold funds or digital assets for technical purposes solely to:

secure performance of the agreement;
manage risks;
prevent fraud;
resolve disputes;
comply with law or partner requirements.

Such holding:

is not a financial or custodial service;
is limited in duration;
is carried out only within the transaction or Platform balance.

Terms.s7Content:
The Operator is entitled to charge a commission for use of the Platform.

The commission may include:

commission on conclusion of an agreement;
commission on payment processing;
commission on payouts;
other service fees.

The amount of the commission is determined by the Platform.

Terms.s8Content:
The Platform may require user identification in accordance with legal requirements, banks, payment providers, or risk policies.

Identification may include:

identity document;
proof of address;
biometric verification (selfie);
other documents or data.

Identification may be carried out through third-party providers.

The user agrees to the processing and transfer of personal data to such providers.

Failure to complete KYC may result in:

restriction of functions;
delay or refusal of payout;
blocking of access.

Terms.s9Content:
The Platform may:

verify transactions;
block suspicious operations;
suspend payouts;
require additional confirmation;
notify competent authorities where required by law.

Terms.s10Content:
The Operator has the right at its sole discretion, without prior notice and without giving reasons (within the law):

to block or suspend accounts;
to restrict functions;
to withhold balance;
to delay or refuse payout;
to stop transactions.

Decisions of the Platform regarding security, risks, or breaches are final within the Platform.

Terms.s12Content:
Users are prohibited from:

using stolen or unauthorized accounts;
fraud or manipulation;
money laundering;
violating the law;
violating third-party rights;
circumventing the Platform's security systems.

Terms.s13Content:
The Operator is not liable for:

actions or inaction of users;
non-performance of agreements;
blocking of accounts in video games;
loss of digital assets;
loss of funds;
actions of third parties;
technical failures or unavailability of services.

The Platform is provided "as is".

AmlCompliance.s2Content:
The Platform complies with:

Ukrainian legislation in the field of financial monitoring;
international AML/CTF standards;
requirements of banks, payment providers, and partners;
sanctions regimes and export restrictions (where applicable).

AmlCompliance.s3Content:
The Operator carries out:

user risk assessment;
transaction monitoring;
review of suspicious operations;
control of source of funds;
sanctions and compliance screening;
fraud prevention measures.

The level of verification depends on the user's or transaction's risk profile.

AmlCompliance.s4Content:
The Platform may:

analyze transactions;
detect suspicious patterns;
review activity history;
use automated risk-analysis systems;
check data against sanctions lists or risk databases.

Monitoring is carried out continuously during use of the Platform.

AmlCompliance.s5Content:
The Platform may require user identification.

KYC may include:

identity document;
proof of address;
selfie or biometric verification;
proof of account ownership;
other data for risk assessment.

Identification may be carried out by third-party providers.

AmlCompliance.s6Content:
The Platform may require documents or information on the origin of funds or assets, including:

bank statements;
transaction history;
proof of income;
history of acquisition of digital assets;
other supporting materials.

Failure to provide information may result in restrictions.

AmlCompliance.s7Content:
The Platform has the right to:

monitor transactions;
require documents or explanations;
suspend transactions;
withhold or freeze balance;
delay or refuse payout;
restrict account functions;
block accounts;
disclose information to competent authorities;
comply with requirements of banks or partners.

AmlCompliance.s8Content:
The Platform may:

check users against sanctions;
restrict access from certain jurisdictions;
block users on sanctions lists;
refuse transactions with sanctions risk.

AmlCompliance.s9Content:
The user agrees to:

not use the Platform for illegal operations;
not engage in money laundering;
not finance illegal activity;
provide accurate data;
provide requested information;
undergo AML/KYC checks;
agree to transaction monitoring;
accept the possibility of checks and restrictions.

AmlCompliance.s10Content:
The Platform may temporarily suspend operations or block accounts until AML/CTF or compliance checks are completed.

Decisions regarding:

suspicious transactions;
risks;
compliance;
blocking;
withholding of funds

are final within the Platform (within the law).

AmlCompliance.s11Content:
The Platform may disclose information to:

law enforcement;
financial regulators;
banks or payment institutions;
AML/KYC partners,

where necessary to comply with the law or compliance requirements.

AmlCompliance.s12Content:
Failure to meet AML/KYC or compliance requirements may result in:

restriction of functions;
suspension of operations;
freezing of balance;
refusal of payout;
blocking of account;
notification of competent authorities.

Privacy.s3Content:
Personal data is processed for:

providing access to the Platform;
performance of agreements between users;
processing transactions;
fraud prevention;
securing the Platform;
conducting KYC/AML checks;
compliance with legal requirements;
communication with the user;
resolving disputes;
protection of the Operator's rights.

Privacy.s4Content:
Personal data is processed on the basis of:

performance of contract (provision of the Platform service);
legitimate interests of the Operator (security, fraud prevention);
legal obligations (AML/KYC, authority requirements);
user consent (where required).

Privacy.s5Content:
Personal data may be disclosed to:

payment providers;
identification services (KYC);
hosting providers;
security and anti-fraud services;
banks and financial partners;
state or regulatory bodies (where required by law).

Disclosure is made only to the extent necessary for the respective purposes.

Privacy.s6Content:
We collect and process personal data for:

identity verification (KYC);
compliance with AML/CTF requirements;
fraud prevention;
risk management;
disclosure to verification services.

KYC data may be verified by third-party providers.

Failure to complete KYC may result in:

restriction of functions;
delay or refusal of payout;
blocking of the account.

Privacy.s7Content:
Data may be transferred outside Ukraine or the EEA where necessary for:

hosting;
payments;
KYC/AML checks;
security.

In such cases, appropriate data protection safeguards apply (standard contractual clauses or equivalent mechanisms).

Privacy.s8Content:
Personal data is retained:

for the duration of account use;
for periods required for financial monitoring;
for dispute resolution;
for compliance with legal requirements.

After the applicable periods, data is deleted or anonymized.

Privacy.s9Content:
The user has the right to:

access their data;
rectify data;
erase data (where possible);
restrict processing;
object to processing;
receive a copy of data;
lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.

Some rights may be limited by AML/KYC or financial monitoring requirements.

Privacy.s10Content:
The Operator applies technical and organizational measures:

encryption;
access control;
server security;
security monitoring;
minimization of access to data.

Privacy.s11Content:
The Platform uses cookies for:

authentication;
security;
service operation;
analytics.

The user may manage cookies through browser settings.

CryptoRisk.s2Content:
Crypto assets are characterized by high volatility.

Their market value may:

change sharply;
decrease to zero;
fluctuate significantly in a short time.

The user may lose the entire value of their crypto assets.

CryptoRisk.s3Content:
Transactions involving crypto assets are generally irreversible.

Crypto assets may be irreversibly lost in the event of:

address error;
loss of access to wallet;
fraud;
technical failures;
actions of third parties;
compromise of keys or accounts.

Recovery of crypto assets may be impossible.

CryptoRisk.s4Content:
Crypto ecosystems depend on blockchain technology, networks, and software.

Possible risks include:

network failures;
transaction delays;
smart contract errors;
attacks or breaches;
data loss;
protocol errors.

The Platform does not control blockchain networks.

CryptoRisk.s5Content:
The legal status of crypto assets may change.

Possible:

restrictions or prohibitions;
regulatory requirements;
tax implications;
blocking of services;
sanctions restrictions.

Such changes may affect the availability or use of crypto assets.

CryptoRisk.s6Content:
Crypto assets:

are not legal tender in most jurisdictions;
are not backed by the state;
are not covered by state insurance;
are not protected by deposit guarantee schemes.

The value of crypto assets is not guaranteed.

CryptoRisk.s7Content:
As the Platform is a P2P service:

transactions are between users;
there is a risk of non-performance;
fraud is possible;
disputes or losses may occur.

The Platform does not guarantee performance of transactions.

CryptoRisk.s8Content:
Information on the Platform is not:

investment advice;
financial recommendation;
an offer to buy or sell;
investment consulting.

The user makes decisions independently.

CryptoRisk.s9Content:
The user is solely responsible for:

assessment of crypto asset risks;
security of wallets and keys;
verification of addresses and transactions;
legality of operations;
tax obligations.

CryptoRisk.s10Content:
The Platform is not liable for:

loss of crypto assets;
changes in their value;
blockchain technical failures;
actions of third parties;
user errors;
regulatory consequences;
non-performance of P2P transactions.

CryptoRisk.s11Content:
By using the Platform, the User confirms that:

they understand the risks of crypto assets;
they accept the possibility of total loss;
they act at their own risk;
they do not rely on the Platform as a financial intermediary.

CookiePolicy.s3Content:
Our Platform may use cookies set by third parties, including:

• Payment and crypto providers — to process transactions, verify payments, and secure checkout flows;
• Authentication providers (e.g. Google) — to enable sign-in features;
• Analytics services — to measure usage and improve the Platform;
• Security and fraud prevention services — to protect users and detect suspicious activity.

Third-party cookies are essential for crypto and payment operations. They enable secure authentication, transaction verification, and compliance with regulatory requirements. By using the Platform, you acknowledge that these third-party cookies may be placed on your device.

CookiePolicy.s4Content:
You can control or delete cookies through your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to:

• Block all cookies;
• Block third-party cookies only;
• Delete existing cookies.

Please note: blocking essential or security cookies may prevent the Platform from functioning correctly. You may not be able to log in, complete transactions, or use payment features if essential cookies are disabled.

CookiePolicy.s5Content:
By continuing to use the Platform, you consent to our use of cookies in accordance with this policy.

You may withdraw or change your consent at any time by:

• Adjusting your browser settings to block or delete cookies;
• Using any cookie preference tools we provide on the Platform;
• Contacting us via the Contact us page.

We will respect your preferences. Note that withdrawing consent for essential cookies may limit or prevent your use of the Platform.

Disclaimer.content:
The Platform is an online marketplace that provides technical infrastructure for posting information, interaction, and concluding agreements between users.

The Platform Operator acts solely as a technological intermediary and is not a seller, buyer, broker, agent, escrow agent, financial institution, or party to any agreements between users.

All agreements, arrangements, transactions, and settlements are made directly between users at their own risk and responsibility.

No control or liability for goods and content

The Operator does not control, verify, guarantee, or approve:

• goods, services, or digital assets posted by users;
• the legality of ownership or transfer of assets;
• the quality, safety, legality, authenticity, or fitness of assets;
• the accuracy of information in listings.

The Platform is not affiliated with video game developers, publishers, rights holders, or other third parties related to digital products that may be offered by users.

P2P nature of transactions

Users acknowledge and agree that:

• the Platform does not sell or buy assets;
• the Platform is not the owner of assets;
• the Platform does not guarantee performance of transactions;
• the Platform does not ensure the legality of asset transfers;
• the Platform does not act as a party to disputes between users.

All risks related to transactions, including loss of assets or funds, are borne solely by users.

Status of user funds and balance

Funds displayed on the user's balance within the Platform are an internal accounting record of the Platform reflecting the amount available for payout to the user.

Until actual withdrawal of funds:

• funds may be held or processed in the Operator's or payment providers' bank accounts;
• funds are not considered transferred to the user's actual possession outside the Platform;
• the user has only the right to request a payout in accordance with the Platform's rules.

The Platform is not a bank, payment institution, or escrow service.

Platform's right to block and withhold

The Operator has the right at its sole discretion, at any time, without prior notice and without giving reasons (within applicable law):

• to block or suspend accounts;
• to restrict access to features;
• to cancel or stop transactions;
• to withhold or freeze balance;
• to delay or refuse payout of funds;
• to restrict or terminate access to assets.

Such measures may be applied in particular in case of:

• suspicion of fraud or abuse;
• breach of Platform rules;
• disputes between users;
• risk of payment chargebacks;
• requirements of banks, payment providers, or regulators;
• sanctions or AML/KYC risks;
• infringement of third-party or intellectual property rights;
• any risks or liability for the Platform.

Finality of Platform decisions

Decisions of the Operator regarding:

• blocking or restricting access;
• withholding or freezing funds;
• refusal of payout;
• access to the Platform or assets

are final within the Platform.

The Operator is not obliged to:

• provide explanations;
• conduct investigations;
• participate in user disputes;
• restore access or assets.

No advice

The Platform does not provide financial, investment, legal, tax, or other professional advice.

No information on the Platform constitutes an offer or recommendation to buy or sell:

• crypto assets;
• digital assets;
• financial instruments;
• investment products.

User responsibility for legality

Users are solely responsible for:

• the legality of acquiring and transferring assets;
• compliance with video game and service rules;
• tax obligations;
• foreign exchange regulation;
• compliance with sanctions and export restrictions;
• third-party intellectual property rights.

Disclaimer of warranties and liability

The Platform is provided "as is" and "as available".

The Operator does not guarantee:

• uninterrupted or error-free operation;
• availability of the Platform;
• preservation of data;
• success of transactions;
• preservation of assets or funds.

The Operator is not liable for any:

• direct or indirect damages;
• loss of funds or assets;
• loss of profit or opportunities;
• blocking or loss of access;
• actions or inaction of users.

Acceptance of terms

By using the Platform, the user confirms that:

• they have read this Marketplace Disclaimer;
• they understand the P2P nature of the Platform;
• they accept the Platform's right to block and withhold;
• they use the Platform at their own risk.
